subSubSection.paragraph:
Male (
Figure 22
) diagnosed by
Gray ( 1994 )
. Females can be distinguished by the combination of widened and triangular bases of the spermathecae and inner spermathecae positioned laterally (rather than anteriorly) to the outer spermathecae (
Figures 23
C – E, 24 B, C).

(D) Spermathecae and genital aperture, dorsal, cleared. (E) Right spermathecae, ventral, cleared. (F) Female (subadult?) from Port Hedland Salt, Western Australia (WAM T76810), spermathecae, dorsal, cleared. Abbreviations: Bs, base of the spermathecae; IS, inner spermathecae; OS, outer spermathecae.
